43namespace webrtc {
44
45class FrameEncryptorInterface;
46class RtpPacketizer;
47class RtpPacketToSend;
48
49// kConditionallyRetransmitHigherLayers allows retransmission of video frames
50// in higher layers if either the last frame in that layer was too far back in
51// time, or if we estimate that a new frame will be available in a lower layer
52// in a shorter time than it would take to request and receive a retransmission.
53enum RetransmissionMode : uint8_t {
54 kRetransmitOff = 0x0,
55 kRetransmitBaseLayer = 0x2,
56 kRetransmitHigherLayers = 0x4,
57 kRetransmitAllLayers = 0x6,
58 kConditionallyRetransmitHigherLayers = 0x8
59};
60
61class RTPSenderVideo {
62 public:
63 static constexpr int64_t kTLRateWindowSizeMs = 2500;
64
65 struct Config {
66 Config() = default;
67 Config(const Config&) = delete;
68 Config(Config&&) = default;
69
70 // All members of this struct, with the exception of |field_trials|, are
71 // expected to outlive the RTPSenderVideo object they are passed to.
72 Clock* clock = nullptr;
73 RTPSender* rtp_sender = nullptr;
74 // Some FEC data is duplicated here in preparation of moving FEC to
75 // the egress stage.
76 absl::optional<VideoFecGenerator::FecType> fec_type;
77 size_t fec_overhead_bytes = 0; // Per packet max FEC overhead.
78 FrameEncryptorInterface* frame_encryptor = nullptr;
79 bool require_frame_encryption = false;
80 bool enable_retransmit_all_layers = false;
81 absl::optional<int> red_payload_type;
82 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* field_trials = nullptr;
83 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer;
84 TaskQueueBase* send_transport_queue = nullptr;
85 };
86
87 explicit RTPSenderVideo(const Config& config);
88
89 virtual ~RTPSenderVideo();
90
91 // expected_retransmission_time_ms.has_value() -> retransmission allowed.
92 // Calls to this method is assumed to be externally serialized.
93 // |estimated_capture_clock_offset_ms| is an estimated clock offset between
94 // this sender and the original capturer, for this video packet. See
95 // http://www.webrtc.org/experiments/rtp-hdrext/abs-capture-time for more
96 // details. If the sender and the capture has the same clock, it is supposed
97 // to be zero valued, which is given as the default.
98 bool SendVideo(int payload_type,
99 absl::optional<VideoCodecType> codec_type,
100 uint32_t rtp_timestamp,
101 int64_t capture_time_ms,
102 rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> payload,
103 RTPVideoHeader video_header,
104 absl::optional<int64_t> expected_retransmission_time_ms,
105 absl::optional<int64_t> estimated_capture_clock_offset_ms = 0);
106
107 bool SendEncodedImage(
108 int payload_type,
109 absl::optional<VideoCodecType> codec_type,
110 uint32_t rtp_timestamp,
111 const EncodedImage& encoded_image,
112 RTPVideoHeader video_header,
113 absl::optional<int64_t> expected_retransmission_time_ms);
114
115 // Configures video structures produced by encoder to send using the
116 // dependency descriptor rtp header extension. Next call to SendVideo should
117 // have video_header.frame_type == kVideoFrameKey.
118 // All calls to SendVideo after this call must use video_header compatible
119 // with the video_structure.
120 void SetVideoStructure(const FrameDependencyStructure* video_structure);
121 // Should only be used by a RTPSenderVideoFrameTransformerDelegate and exists
122 // to ensure correct syncronization.
123 void SetVideoStructureAfterTransformation(
124 const FrameDependencyStructure* video_structure);
125
126 // Sets current active VideoLayersAllocation. The allocation will be sent
127 // using the rtp video layers allocation extension. The allocation will be
128 // sent in full on every key frame. The allocation will be sent once on a
129 // none discardable delta frame per call to this method and will not contain
130 // resolution and frame rate.
131 void SetVideoLayersAllocation(VideoLayersAllocation allocation);
132 // Should only be used by a RTPSenderVideoFrameTransformerDelegate and exists
133 // to ensure correct syncronization.
134 void SetVideoLayersAllocationAfterTransformation(
135 VideoLayersAllocation allocation);
136
137 // Returns the current packetization overhead rate, in bps. Note that this is
138 // the payload overhead, eg the VP8 payload headers, not the RTP headers
139 // or extension/
140 // TODO(sprang): Consider moving this to RtpSenderEgress so it's in the same
141 // place as the other rate stats.
142 uint32_t PacketizationOverheadBps() const;
143
144 protected:
145 static uint8_t GetTemporalId(const RTPVideoHeader& header);
146 bool AllowRetransmission(uint8_t temporal_id,
147 int32_t retransmission_settings,
148 int64_t expected_retransmission_time_ms);
149
150 private:
151 struct TemporalLayerStats {
152 TemporalLayerStats()
153 : frame_rate_fp1000s(kTLRateWindowSizeMs, 1000 * 1000),
154 last_frame_time_ms(0) {}
155 // Frame rate, in frames per 1000 seconds. This essentially turns the fps
156 // value into a fixed point value with three decimals. Improves precision at
157 // low frame rates.
158 RateStatistics frame_rate_fp1000s;
159 int64_t last_frame_time_ms;
160 };
161
162 enum class SendVideoLayersAllocation {
163 kSendWithResolution,
164 kSendWithoutResolution,
165 kDontSend
166 };
167
168 void SetVideoStructureInternal(
169 const FrameDependencyStructure* video_structure);
170 void SetVideoLayersAllocationInternal(VideoLayersAllocation allocation);
171
172 void AddRtpHeaderExtensions(
173 const RTPVideoHeader& video_header,
174 const absl::optional<AbsoluteCaptureTime>& absolute_capture_time,
175 bool first_packet,
176 bool last_packet,
177 RtpPacketToSend* packet) const
178 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(send_checker_);
179
180 size_t FecPacketOverhead() const RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(send_checker_);
181
182 void LogAndSendToNetwork(
183 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets,
184 size_t unpacketized_payload_size);
185
186 bool red_enabled() const { return red_payload_type_.has_value(); }
187
188 bool UpdateConditionalRetransmit(uint8_t temporal_id,
189 int64_t expected_retransmission_time_ms)
190 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(stats_mutex_);
191
192 void MaybeUpdateCurrentPlayoutDelay(const RTPVideoHeader& header)
193 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(send_checker_);
194
195 RTPSender* const rtp_sender_;
196 Clock* const clock_;
197
198 const int32_t retransmission_settings_;
199
200 // These members should only be accessed from within SendVideo() to avoid
201 // potential race conditions.
202 rtc::RaceChecker send_checker_;
203 VideoRotation last_rotation_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_checker_);
204 absl::optional<ColorSpace> last_color_space_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_checker_);
205 bool transmit_color_space_next_frame_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_checker_);
206 std::unique_ptr<FrameDependencyStructure> video_structure_
207 RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_checker_);
208 absl::optional<VideoLayersAllocation> allocation_
209 RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_checker_);
210 // Flag indicating if we should send |allocation_|.
211 SendVideoLayersAllocation send_allocation_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_checker_);
212
213 // Current target playout delay.
214 VideoPlayoutDelay current_playout_delay_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_checker_);
215 // Flag indicating if we need to send |current_playout_delay_| in order
216 // to guarantee it gets delivered.
217 bool playout_delay_pending_;
218 // Set by the field trial WebRTC-ForceSendPlayoutDelay to override the playout
219 // delay of outgoing video frames.
220 const absl::optional<VideoPlayoutDelay> forced_playout_delay_;
221
222 // Should never be held when calling out of this class.
223 Mutex mutex_;
224
225 const absl::optional<int> red_payload_type_;
226 absl::optional<VideoFecGenerator::FecType> fec_type_;
227 const size_t fec_overhead_bytes_; // Per packet max FEC overhead.
228
229 mutable Mutex stats_mutex_;
230 RateStatistics packetization_overhead_bitrate_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(stats_mutex_);
231
232 std::map<int, TemporalLayerStats> frame_stats_by_temporal_layer_
233 RTC_GUARDED_BY(stats_mutex_);
234
235 OneTimeEvent first_frame_sent_;
236
237 // E2EE Custom Video Frame Encryptor (optional)
238 FrameEncryptorInterface* const frame_encryptor_ = nullptr;
239 // If set to true will require all outgoing frames to pass through an
240 // initialized frame_encryptor_ before being sent out of the network.
241 // Otherwise these payloads will be dropped.
242 const bool require_frame_encryption_;
243 // Set to true if the generic descriptor should be authenticated.
244 const bool generic_descriptor_auth_experiment_;
245
246 AbsoluteCaptureTimeSender absolute_capture_time_sender_;
247 // Tracks updates to the active decode targets and decides when active decode
248 // targets bitmask should be attached to the dependency descriptor.
249 ActiveDecodeTargetsHelper active_decode_targets_tracker_;
250
251 const rtc::scoped_refptr<RTPSenderVideoFrameTransformerDelegate>
252 frame_transformer_delegate_;
253
254 const bool include_capture_clock_offset_;
255};
256
257} // namespace webrtc
